    Scope and Contents
Waggoner, retired United States Army Air Corps Lt. Colonel, discusses his experiences during WWII: enlistment, aviation training, overseas training in England, service with the 353rd Fighter Group at Raydon, England, fighter missions, bombing tactics and electronic counter-measures, mechanical problems of airplanes, shooting down planes, R&amp;R in America, relations with the British military, other members of the 353rd Fighter Group, and his personal feelings about war.

12 tapes, 605 mins., 120 pp.
Interview by Bruce E. Kreuger, 1986
